-Modules

  -Color recognition
    -Generate random RGB values
    -Show color
    -Pair triple with one or more of these:
      -Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, violet, pink, cyan
      -Black, white, gray, brown, tan
    -Partition 0-255 into blocks
    -Build decision tree

  -Space definitions
    -left, right, top, bottom, corner, upper, lower, center, middle
    -Also relative space (next to, left/right, above/below, on top/beneath)

  -Image generation
    -Pick a color for the background
    -Add a shape with a color different from the background (or more)
      -Triangle, quadrilateral, pentagon, hexagon, octagon
    -If I send you pixel coordinates, give me control to move the polygon

  -Analyze scene
    -Separate polygons = clusters of edge pixels = connected components
    -For each polygon:
      -Determine number of sides
      -Find color
      -Identify location

  -Interface: ask questions or assert predicates (later, modify image)
    -Parse input sentence
    -Convert parse tree into search algorithm
    -Return algo(collection of descriptors)